                                <condition key="good">
                                  The manuscript is in a good state of preservation. The leaves are intact and the damage is affecting only the binding.
                                  The sewing is broken at the attachment of the second, third, and fourth sewing station with the upper board and at
                                  the attachment of the third and fourth sewing station with the lower board.
                                  Insects caused the losses present on the cover, especially on the spine. The spine is torn and a part is missing at the head.
                                  A tear on the tail edge has been repaired by sewing it with a black thread. The tailband is fragmentary.
                                  Water stains are present on the upper board.
                                </condition>
