                        <bindingDesc>
                          <binding xml:id="binding" contemporary="true Ethiopian">
                            <decoNote xml:id="b1" type="bindingMaterial">
                                  The book is bound in <material key="wood">wooden</material> boards covered with reddish-brown blind-tooled <material
                                  key="leather">leather</material>. The inner sides of the upper and lower boards are decorated with <material key="textile">textile</material> <term key="textileInlay">inlays</term>
                                  with floral pattern in yellow and red colour.
                                </decoNote>
                                <decoNote xml:id="b2" type="Boards">
                                  The boards are cut to the same size as the bookblock and present external shallow bevels.
                                </decoNote>
                                <decoNote xml:id="b3" type="Cover" color="reddish brown">
                                  Full reddish-brown leather cover.
                                  The turn-ins have been trimmed out and at the corners they form butt mitres.
                                  An <term key="additionalLeatherPatch">additional leather patch</term> has been added along the inner margin of the boards to fill the gap between the turn-ins.
                                  The cover shows a fine blind-tooled decoration, identical on both sides of the cover. The turn-ins and the edges are also decorated.
                                  The decoration consists of eleven concentric frames surrounding a central rectangular panel featuring a Latin cross.
                                  Frames composed by the repetition of single tools, enclosed between <term key="tripleStraightLine">triple straight lines</term>,
                                  alternate with empty ones with <term key="doubleCircle">double circles</term> at the corners.
                                  Proceeding from the outer to the inner frame, the repeating decoration motifs are <term key="crissCross">criss-cross</term> (in two variants),
                                  <term key="straightStrapwork">straight strapwork</term> elements, <term key="curveStrapwork">curve strapwork</term> elements, <term key="wavyLine">wavy lines</term>
                                  with <term key="doubleCircle">double circles</term> in the middle, and term <term key="curveStrapwork">curve strapwork</term> elements in a smaller variant.
                                  The cross is formed by <term key="XForm">X-form</term> motifs separated by dots between triple straight lines.
                                  Triple straight lines decorate the turn-ins, outlining the their margins. On the spine, they cross each other diagonally, forming a diamond pattern
                                  with double circles at the intersections. Two <term key="singleStraightLine">single straight lines</term> run along the edges of the boards.
                                </decoNote>
                                <decoNote xml:id="b4" type="Endbands" color="brown">
                                  Brown <term key="slitBraid">slit-braid</term> endbands are present.
                                </decoNote>
                                <decoNote xml:id="b5" type="SewingStations">4</decoNote>
                                <decoNote xml:id="b6">
                                  Chainstitch sewing on four sewing stations (two pairs); periodic fold pattern; Z-plied threads.
                                  Between each pair of sewing stations there are two lengths of thread.
                                </decoNote>
                                <decoNote xml:id="b7" type="Spine">
                                  The spine is formed by two overlapping layers of leather. The endbands are sewn through the first layer so that
                                  the tie-downs are hidden under the second layer.
                                  To obtain a sufficiently wide cover for the boards, two pieces of leather were sewn together and the sewing runs along the spine.
                                </decoNote>
                                <decoNote xml:id="b8" type="Other">
                                  A pink string and a green textile ribbon presumably with the function of bookmarkers are found between the pages.
                                  More specifically, the pink string is between <locus target="#15"/> and <locus target="#16"/>, and
                                  the green ribbon between <locus target="#203"/> and <locus target="#204"/>.
                                </decoNote>
                            </binding>
